## 2026-06-13 — NAVRA-081: Unified semantic permissions (pending_approval)

### What was done
- Audited NAVRA-077 fix, found 5 remaining security flaws in permission system
- Researched 10+ competing MCP gateways/agent frameworks — none does semantic permissions
- Discovered Cedar emerging as standard (AWS Bedrock AgentCore, ToolHive, TrueFoundry, MuleSoft)
- Discovered Microsoft ACS (Agent Control Specification) — OPA/Rego-based alternative
- Designed and implemented domain:operation semantic classification system
- Fixed all 5 security flaws: prompt checks, resource template bypass, CallContext propagation, fail-closed auth, semantic enforcement

### Key artifacts
- NEW: navra-auth/src/permissions/resource_class.rs — Domain/Operation enums, ResourceClass, heuristic classifier, domain exemplars
- NEW: navra-auth/src/permissions/domain_rules.rs — DomainRules evaluation engine
- MOD: navra-core/src/module.rs — PromptHandler/ResourceHandler now receive CallContext (BREAKING)
- MOD: navra-core/src/server/handlers.rs — domain check in handle_call_tool, permission checks for prompts/resources
- MOD: navra-core/src/server/builder.rs — fail-closed auth, auto-classify tools, domain_rules builder methods
- MOD: navra-core/src/upstream_module.rs — embedding-based classifier, tool_classifications accessor
- MOD: navra-server/src/config/permissions.rs — domain_rules, tool_class config fields
- MOD: navra-server/src/main.rs — config wiring, default rule synthesis from operations field

### Decisions
- Domain taxonomy is fixed (enum, not freeform strings) — operators assign, don't invent
- 4-tier classification: operator override > ToolAnnotations > AI embedding > name heuristic
- AI tier uses existing ModelBackend::embed() — graceful degradation when no model loaded
- Default synthesis from operations field — no config = still enforced (fail-closed)
- PromptHandler/ResourceHandler breaking change accepted — defense-in-depth requirement

### Status: PENDING_APPROVAL
Breaking API changes + security architecture change require human review before merge.

